Titolo: I.M. Meen

Anno: 1995

Descrizione: I.M. Meen is a 1995 educational game for DOS to teach grammar to children. The player walks around a labyrinth, rescuing children and defeating monsters. The educational aspect of the game comes in the form of "scrolls", writings of I.M. Meen in which the player must correct the grammatical mistakes in order to rescue the children. The game was created by Russo-American company Animation Magic which also developed the CD-i games Hotel Mario, Link: The Faces of Evil and Zelda: The Wand of Gamelon. Peter Berkrot provided the voice of I.M Meen, while Gnorris was voiced by John Mahon.